Outgoing Polokwane Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) Councillor Len Meyer was arrested yesterday (Thursday) afternoon for allegedly inciting to commit crime following the alleged illegal occupation of land by dwellers in Extension 44 on the road to Ga-Matlala. He was warned to appear in court on 15 September. Westenburg Police spokesperson Mpandeni Nkuna confirmed Meyer&#8217;s arrest on a charge of incitement to commit an offence. He was arrested by detectives attached to the station at around 13:00 yesterday. Nkuna further confirmed that the arrest followed the earlier alleged illegal occupation of land by dwellers along the Matlala Road. Story and photo: YOLANDE NEL &gt;&gt;observer.yolande@gmail.com &nbsp;